base5.name: Dark Alakazam

attacks.name: Teleport Blast
attacks.text: You may switch Dark Alakazam with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

base5.flavorText: Almost as if it were being controlled by something else, it never changes expressions, even in the middle of battle.

base5.name: Dark Arbok

attacks.name: Stare
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.) If that Pokémon has a Pokémon Power, that power stops working until the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Poison Vapor
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base5.flavorText: Freezes its prey with its stare. If you should encounter one, remember not to look into its eyes.

base5.name: Dark Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydrocannon
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Rocket Tackle
attacks.text: Dark Blastoise does 10 damage to itself. Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Dark Blastoise during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

base5.flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.

base5.name: Dark Charizard

attacks.name: Continuous Fireball
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Charizard. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads. Discard a number of Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Charizard equal to the number of heads.

base5.flavorText: Seemingly possessed, it spews fire like a volcano, trying to burn all it sees.

base5.name: Dark Dragonite

abilities.name: Summon Minions
abilities.text: When you play Dark Dragonite from your hand, search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Giant Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

base5.flavorText: Sometimes called "The God of Destruction." Its wings are able to support it in spite of its massive weight.

base5.name: Dark Dugtrio

abilities.name: Sinkhole
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokémon retreats, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this power does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working while Dark Dugtrio is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Knock Down
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if heads, this attack does 20 damage.

base5.flavorText: Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.

base5.name: Dark Golbat

abilities.name: Sneak Attack
abilities.text: When you play Dark Golbat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you do, Dark Golbat does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Flitter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

base5.flavorText: Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.

base5.name: Dark Gyarados

abilities.name: Final Beam
abilities.text: When Dark Gyarados is Knocked Out by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this power does 20 damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Gyarados to the Pokémon that Knocked Out Dark Gyarados. Apply Weakness and Resistance. This power doesn't work if Dark Gyarados is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base5.flavorText: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.

base5.name: Dark Hypno

attacks.name: Bench Manipulation
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a number of coins equal to the number of Pokémon on his or her Bench. This attack does 20 damage times the number of tails. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

base5.flavorText: Carries a pendulum with it always. Sometimes appears near less-traveled roads and schools at dusk.

base5.name: Dark Machamp

attacks.name: Fling
attacks.text: Your opponent shuffles his or her Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her deck. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.

base5.flavorText: It is almost impossible to defend against a Machamp's four powerful arms.

base1.name: Alakazam

abilities.name: Damage Swap
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to another as long as you don't Knock Out that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

base1.flavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5000.

base1.name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokémon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Extra Water Energy after the 2nd doesn't count.

base1.flavorText: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

base1.name: Chansey

attacks.name: Scrunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Chansey during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Chansey does 80 damage to itself.

base1.flavorText: A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch it.

base1.name: Charizard

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard in order to use this attack.

base1.flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

base1.name: Clefairy

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Metronome
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type the Defending Pokémon is, Clefairy's type is still Colorless.)

base1.flavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

base1.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base1.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

base1.name: Hitmonchan
base1.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

base1.name: Machamp

abilities.name: Strikes Back
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent's attack damages Machamp (even if Machamp is Knocked Out), this power does 10 damage to the attacking Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power can't be used if Machamp is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed when your opponent attacks.

base1.flavorText: Using its amazing muscles, it throws powerful punches that can knock its victim clear over the horizon.

base1.name: Magneton

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Selfdestruct
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each Pokémon on each player's Bench. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Magneton does 80 damage to itself.

base1.flavorText: Formed by several Magnemites linked together. It frequently appears when sunspots flare up.

base1.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Barrier
attacks.text: Discard 1 Psychic Energy card attached to Mewtwo in order to prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mewtwo during your opponent's next turn.

base1.flavorText: A scientist created this Pokémon after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

dp1.name: Dialga

attacks.name: Time Bellow
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Flash Cannon
attacks.text: You may return all Energy cards attached to Dialga to your hand. If you do, remove the highest Stage Evolution card from the Defending Pokémon and shuffle that card into your opponent's deck.

dp1.flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

dp1.name: Dusknoir

abilities.name: Dark Palm
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if your opponent has 4 or more Benched Pokémon, you may choose 1 of them and shuffle that Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her deck. This power can't be used if Dusknoir if affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hard Feelings
attacks.text: Put 5 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon. Then, count the number of Prize cards your opponent has taken and put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

dp1.flavorText: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

dp1.name: Electivire

abilities.name: Intense Voltage
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), if Elekid is anywhere under Electivire, you may move a Lightning Energy attached to your Pokémon to Electivire. This power can't be used if Electivire is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Giga Impact
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Electivire. If you do, this attack's base damage is 120 instead of 60.

dp1.flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

dp1.name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Ice Blade
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Aqua Jet
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dp1.flavorText: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

dp1.name: Infernape

attacks.name: Meteor Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Flare Blitz
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Infernape.

dp1.flavorText: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

dp1.name: Lucario

attacks.name: Feint
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dp1.flavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

dp1.name: Luxray

abilities.name: Gleam Eyes
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Luxray from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may look at your opponent's hand. If your opponent's Bench isn't full, choose 1 Basic Pokémon from your opponent's hand, and put it onto his or her Bench. Then, switch it with the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Lightning Star
attacks.text: Move all Lightning Energy attached to Luxray to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Ignore this effect if you don't have any Benched Pokémon.)

dp1.flavorText: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

dp1.name: Magnezone

abilities.name: Magnetize
abilities.text: If you have any Metal Energy attached to your Active Pokémon, the Retreat Cost for that Pokémon is 0.

attacks.name: Metal Blast
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to Magnezone.

dp1.flavorText: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

dp1.name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Aqua Ring
attacks.text: Switch Manaphy with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

dp1.flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

dp1.name: Mismagius

attacks.name: Avenge
attacks.text: Count the number of your Pokémon that have any damage counters on them. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psywave
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

dp1.flavorText: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

si1.name: Mew

attacks.name: Rainbow Wave
attacks.text: Choose a type of Energy other than Colorless attached to Mew. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon of that type (including Benched Pokémon). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon's body is covered by fine hairs that can be seen only under a microscope.

si1.name: Pidgeot

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon searches for food while flying at Mach 2. Its large claws make fearsome weapons.

si1.name: Onix

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon burrows through the earth at high speed, looking for food. The tunnels it digs are used by Diglett as nests.

si1.name: Togepi

attacks.name: Bawl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon is still immature. When threatened, it releases poison from its head and tries to drive its enemies away.

si1.name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Strange Scent
attacks.text: Each player flips a coin. Each player who gets heads chooses a total of 3 damage counters from among his or her Pokémon and removes them. (If the player's Pokémon have fewer total damage counters than that, he or she removes all of them.)

si1.flavorText: A sure sign spring is on its way is when the seed on this Pokémon's back flowers.

si1.name: Raticate

attacks.name: Sharp Teeth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon sometimes hunts for food in rivers, swimming using the small webs between the toes on its rear legs.

si1.name: Ledyba

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Ledyba.

si1.flavorText: When it senses enemies approaching, this Pokémon releases an orange fluid from the joints in its legs and flees.

si1.name: Jigglypuff

attacks.name: Tempting Eyes
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

si1.flavorText: After lulling its enemies with its large eyes, this Pokémon sings them to sleep with a relaxing melody.

si1.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Butterfree. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.name: Rainbow Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

si1.flavorText: The poison scales on its wings are waterproof, allowing this Pokémon to be active even on rainy days.

si1.name: Tentacruel

attacks.name: Tentacle Grip
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Water Energy attached to Tentacruel. For each heads, draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

si1.flavorText: This Pokémon attacks its prey with its eighty toxin-producing tentacles.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Hisuian Voltorb

attacks.name: Cheerful Charge
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to that Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Kricketune

abilities.name: Swelling Tune
abilities.text: Your Grass Pokémon in play, except any Kricketune, get +40 HP. You can't apply more than 1 Swelling Tune Ability at a time.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Boltsplosion
attacks.text: If Electivire is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Oricorio

abilities.name: Lesson in Zeal
abilities.text: All of your Fusion Strike Pokémon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Lesson in Zeal Ability at a time.

attacks.name: Glistening Droplets
attacks.text: Put 5 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Raging Freeze
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Manaphy

abilities.name: Wave Veil
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Keldeo

attacks.name: Line Force
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Electivire

attacks.name: Explosive Bolt
attacks.text: If any of your Benched Magmortar have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.

attacks.name: High-Voltage Current
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Toxtricity

abilities.name: Maximum Downer
abilities.text: If all your Pokémon in play are Fusion Strike Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon VMAX in play get -30 HP.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.

swsh12pt5gg.name: Mew

abilities.name: Mysterious Tail
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

swsh12pt5gg.flavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

sv4pt5.name: Pineco
sv4pt5.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

sv4pt5.name: Forretress ex
rules: Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Exploding Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv4pt5.name: Magmar

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

sv4pt5.flavorText: These Pokémon's bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

sv4pt5.name: Maractus

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

sv4pt5.flavorText: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

sv4pt5.name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Volcanic Heat
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

sv4pt5.flavorText: Living in the crater of a volcano has caused this Pokémon's body to resemble its environment— it has an organ similar to a magma chamber.

sv4pt5.name: Heat Rotom

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

sv4pt5.flavorText: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.

sv4pt5.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Into the Deep
attacks.text: Put up to 3 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Freeze-Dry
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

sv4pt5.flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

sv4pt5.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv4pt5.flavorText: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

sv4pt5.name: Camerupt

attacks.name: Super Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Cinder Cannon
attacks.text: You may discard a Fighting Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage.

sv4pt5.flavorText: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

sv4pt5.name: Charcadet
sv4pt5.flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

base3.name: Aerodactyl

abilities.name: Prehistoric Power
abilities.text: No more Evolution cards can be played. This power stops working while Aerodactyl is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

base3.flavorText: A ferocious prehistoric Pokémon that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

base3.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Freeze Dry
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base3.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

base3.name: Ditto

abilities.name: Transform
abilities.text: If Ditto is your Active Pokémon, treat it as if it were the same card as the Defending Pokémon, including type, Hit Points, Weakness, and so on, except Ditto can't evolve, always has this Pokémon Power, and you may treat any Energy attached to Ditto as Energy of any type. Ditto isn't a copy of any other Pokémon while Ditto is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

base3.flavorText: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

base3.name: Dragonite

abilities.name: Step In
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Dragonite is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

base3.flavorText: An extremely rarely seen marine Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

base3.name: Gengar

abilities.name: Curse
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon to another (even if it would Knock Out the other Pokémon). This power can't be used if Gengar is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Dark Mind
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base3.flavorText: Under a full moon, this Pokémon likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

base3.name: Haunter

abilities.name: Transparency
abilities.text: Whenever an attack does anything to Haunter, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of that attack, including damage, done to Haunter. This power stops working while Haunter is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Nightmare
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

base3.flavorText: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

base3.name: Hitmonlee

attacks.name: Stretch Kick
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base3.flavorText: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

base3.name: Hypno

attacks.name: Prophecy
attacks.text: Look at up to 3 cards from the top of either player's deck and rearrange them as you like.

attacks.name: Dark Mind
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base3.flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

base3.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from Kabutops equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Kabutops has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

base3.flavorText: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

base3.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Lapras but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

base3.flavorText: A Pokémon that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across water.

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Ho-Oh.

attacks.name: Aerowing
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, this attack does 60 damage instead.

attacks.name: Copy

(Has no effect other than providing Energy.) Damage done to your opponent's Pokémon by the Pokémon Double Rainbow Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). When the Pokémon Double Rainbow Energy is attached to is no longer an Evolved Pokémon, discard Double Rainbow Energy.

pop5.name: Rare Candy
rules: Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 1 or Stage 2 card that evolves from that Pokémon in your hand, put that card on the Basic Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.)

pop5.name: Boost Energy
rules: Boost Energy can be attached only to an Evolved Pokémon. Discard Boost Energy at the end of the turn it was attached. Boost Energy provides ColorlessColorlessColorless Energy. The Pokémon Boost Energy is attached to can't retreat. If the Pokémon Boost Energy is attached to isn't an Evolved Pokémon, discard Boost Energy.

pop5.name: δ Rainbow Energy
rules: δ Rainbow Energy provides Colorless Energy. While attached to a Pokémon that has δ on its card, δ Rainbow Energy provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Has no effect other than providing Energy.)

abilities.name: Pollen Defense
abilities.text: If an attack does damage to Erika's Vileplume while it's your Active Pokémon (even if it's Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. This power works even while Erika's Vileplume is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: If Erika's Vileplume does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), remove a number of damage counters from Erika's Vileplume equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Erika's Vileplume has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Charge
attacks.text: Take up to 2 Lightning Energy cards from your discard pile and attach them to Lt. Surge's Electabuzz.

attacks.name: Discharge
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Lt. Surge's Electabuzz in order to use this attack. Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Lightning Energy cards you discarded. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Repeating Drill
attacks.text: Flip 5 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Energy Charge
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), if Lt. Surge's Magneton is your Active Pokémon, you may take 1 Lightning Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon and attach it to Lt. Surge's Magneton. This power can't be used if Lt. Surge's Magneton is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Lt. Surge's Magneton does 20 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Knockout Needle
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 60 more damage. If 1 or both of them are tails, this attack does 30 damage.

abilities.name: Flee
abilities.text: If an attack does damage to Misty's Tentacruel while it's your Active Pokémon, you may switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokémon, which prevents all other effects of that attack on Misty's Tentacruel. This power can't be used if Misty's Tentacruel is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Jellyfish Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

sv7.name: Venusaur ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Tranquil Flower
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may heal 60 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dangerous Toxwhip
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

abilities.name: Glittering Star Pattern
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has 90 HP or less remaining to the Active Spot.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

abilities.name: Selective Slime
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose Burned, Confused, or Poisoned. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition.

attacks.name: Miasma Wind
attacks.text: This attack does 100 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Nosh
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Loom Over
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Reaping Dash
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools and Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard 1 Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Rayquaza during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Cling
attacks.text: After your attack, remove from Sceptile the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to the Defending Pokémon. If Sceptile has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mud Splash
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Beautifly.

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

abilities.name: Insomnia
abilities.text: Murkrow can't be Asleep.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rock Smash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Amnesia
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

swsh11tg.name: Parasect

abilities.name: Lethargy Spores
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may make both Active Pokémon Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect's actions.

swsh11tg.name: Roserade

attacks.name: Poisonous Whip
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Assassin's Rose
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

swsh11tg.flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

swsh11tg.name: Charizard

abilities.name: Battle Sense
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Discard the other cards.

attacks.name: Royal Blaze
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Leon card in your discard pile.

swsh11tg.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

swsh11tg.name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Mountain Roasting
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

swsh11tg.flavorText: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

swsh11tg.name: Pikachu

abilities.name: Pika Dash
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Whimsy Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

swsh11tg.name: Gengar

abilities.name: Netherworld Gate
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Screaming Circle
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!

swsh11tg.name: Banette

attacks.name: Resolute Spite
attacks.text: Put up to 7 damage counters on this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.

attacks.name: Eerie Light
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

swsh11tg.name: Hisuian Arcanine

attacks.name: Very Vulnerable
attacks.text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 150 more damage.

swsh11tg.flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

swsh11tg.name: Spiritomb

abilities.name: Cursed Message
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Chain of Spirits
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

swsh11tg.flavorText: It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokémon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.

swsh11tg.name: Snorlax

abilities.name: Unfazed Fat
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

attacks.name: Thumping Snore
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. During Pokémon Checkup, flip 2 coins instead of 1. If either of them is tails, this Pokémon is still Asleep.

swsh11tg.flavorText: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.

sm7.name: Bellsprout

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

sm7.flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

sm7.name: Weepinbell

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Razor Leaf
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

sm7.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

sm7.name: Victreebel

abilities.name: Fragrance Trap
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Corrosive Acid
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

sm7.flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

sm7.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Twin Play
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Scyther and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

sm7.flavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

sm7.name: Spinarak

attacks.name: Stun Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

sm7.name: Ariados

attacks.name: Reactive Poison
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spider Trap
attacks.text: You may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

sm7.name: Treecko

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

sm7.flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

sm7.name: Treecko
sm7.flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

sm7.name: Grovyle

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

sm7.flavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

sm7.name: Sceptile

abilities.name: Power of Nature
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Pokémon that have any Grass Energy attached to them by attacks from your opponent's Ultra Beasts.

attacks.name: Powerful Storm
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

sm7.flavorText: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

hgss3.name: Bellossom

abilities.name: Hustle Step
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Bellossom is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Dance 'til Dawn
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. Bellossom is now Asleep.

hgss3.flavorText: Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

hgss3.name: Espeon

attacks.name: Solar Suggestion
attacks.text: Move up to 4 damage counters from any of your Pokémon to any of your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

hgss3.flavorText: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy's actions.

hgss3.name: Forretress

attacks.name: Mirror Shot
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Everyone Explode Now
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of Pineco and Forretress you have in play. This attack does 30 damage to each of your Pineco and Forretress in play.

hgss3.flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

hgss3.name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Ninja Fang
attacks.text: If, before Gliscor does damage, the Defending Pokémon has no damage counters on it and is then damaged by this attack (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

hgss3.flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

hgss3.name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Fire Counterattack
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Fighting Pokémon in play, this attack does 20 damage plus 60 more damage.

attacks.name: Dark Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent discards a card from his or her hand.

hgss3.flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

hgss3.name: Magcargo

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Lava Flow
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to Magcargo. If you do , this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded.

hgss3.flavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

hgss3.name: Scizor
hgss3.flavorText: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

hgss3.name: Smeargle

abilities.name: Portrait
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Smeargle is your Active Pokémon, you may look at your opponent's hand. If you do, choose a Supporter card you find there and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. This power can't be used if Smeargle is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Tail Rap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

hgss3.flavorText: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

hgss3.name: Togekiss

attacks.name: Blessed Wings
attacks.text: Remove all damage counters from each of your Pokémon. Shuffle Togekiss and all cards attached to it back into your deck.

attacks.name: Air Cutter
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

hgss3.flavorText: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.

hgss3.name: Umbreon

attacks.name: Moonlight Fang
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects, including damage, done to Umbreon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that has any Poké-Powers or Poké-Bodies.

attacks.name: Quick Blow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 damage.

hgss3.flavorText: When agitated, this Pokémon protects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.

swsh8.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Flock
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Caterpie and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh8.flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

swsh8.name: Metapod

abilities.name: Exoskeleton
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

swsh8.flavorText: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.

swsh8.name: Butterfree

abilities.name: Tricolored Scales
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

swsh8.flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

swsh8.name: Shroomish
swsh8.flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

swsh8.name: Breloom V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Counter
attacks.text: If this Pokémon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does that much more damage.

swsh8.name: Breloom

attacks.name: Impact Blow
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Impact Blow.

swsh8.flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

swsh8.name: Pansage
swsh8.flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

swsh8.name: Simisage

attacks.name: Return
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

swsh8.flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

swsh8.name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Grass Munch
attacks.text: Discard a Grass Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

swsh8.flavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

swsh8.name: Swadloon

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

swsh8.flavorText: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

pop9.name: Garchomp

attacks.name: Dragon Rage
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Jet Sword
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Garchomp and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop9.flavorText: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

pop9.name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Dive
attacks.text: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck, choose 1 of them, and put it into your hand. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Water Glow
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Remove from Manaphy the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to that Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pop9.name: Raichu

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: High Volt
attacks.text: If Raichu evolved from Pikachu during this turn, this attack's base damage is 100 instead of 60.

pop9.flavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

pop9.name: Regigigas

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Double Stomp
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

pop9.flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

pop9.name: Rotom

abilities.name: Type Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Rotom's type is Psychic until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Poltergeist
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Trainer, Supporter, and Stadium card in your opponent's hand.

pop9.flavorText: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

pop9.name: Buizel

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Super Fast
attacks.text: If you have Pachirisu in play, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Buizel during your opponent's next turn.

pop9.flavorText: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

pop9.name: Croagunk

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Nimble
attacks.text: If you have Turtwig in play, remove from Croagunk the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

pop9.name: Gabite

attacks.name: Burrow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Gabite by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Distored Wave
attacks.text: Before doing damage, remove 2 damage counters from the Defending Pokémon.

pop9.flavorText: It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.

pop9.name: Lopunny

attacks.name: Jump Kick
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Jazzed
attacks.text: If Lopunny evolved from Buneary during this turn, remove all damage counters from Lopunny.

pop9.flavorText: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

pop9.name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Berry
attacks.text: If you have Croagunk in play, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

pop9.flavorText: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It live atop trees.

base4.name: Alakazam

abilities.name: Damage Swap
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to another as long as you don't Knock Out that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

base4.flavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5000.

base4.name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokémon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

base4.flavorText: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

base4.name: Chansey

attacks.name: Scrunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Chansey during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Chansey does 80 damage to itself.

base4.flavorText: A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch it.

base4.name: Charizard

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard in order to use this attack.

base4.flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

base4.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Metronome
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type the Defending Pokémon is, Clefable's type is still Colorless.)

attacks.name: Minimize
attacks.text: All damage done by attacks to Clefable during your opponent's next turn is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

base4.flavorText: A timid Fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

base4.name: Clefairy

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Metronome
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type the Defending Pokémon is, Clefairy's type is still Colorless.)

base4.flavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

base4.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

base4.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

base4.name: Hitmonchan
base4.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

base4.name: Magneton

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Selfdestruct
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each player's Bench. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Magneton does 80 damage to itself.

base4.flavorText: Formed by several Magnemites linked together. It frequently appears when sunspots flare up.

base4.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Barrier
attacks.text: Discard 1 Psychic Energy card attached to Mewtwo in order to use this attack. During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mewtwo.

base4.flavorText: A scientist created this Pokémon after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

sv2.name: Hoppip

attacks.name: Splashing Dodge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

sv2.flavorText: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

sv2.name: Skiploom

abilities.name: Drifting Dodge
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Flowery Zephyr
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon's head.

sv2.name: Pineco
sv2.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

sv2.name: Jumpluff

abilities.name: Drifting Dodge
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Fluffy Breeze
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

sv2.name: Tropius

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tropic Breeze
attacks.text: Move all Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

sv2.flavorText: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

sv2.name: Forretress ex
rules: Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Exploding Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv2.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Smashing Horn
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

sv2.flavorText: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

sv2.name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Gather Sunlight
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

sv2.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

sv2.name: Sprigatito
sv2.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

sv2.name: Floragato

attacks.name: Magic Whip
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

sv2.flavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

sm1.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

sm1.name: Metapod

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

sm1.flavorText: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.

sm1.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.

sm1.name: Paras
sm1.flavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

sm1.name: Parasect

attacks.name: Fury Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 120 damage.

attacks.name: Mushroom Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

sm1.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Roof Fling
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put your opponent's Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your opponent's hand.

sm1.flavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

sm1.name: Surskit

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

sm1.flavorText: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its heads. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.

sm1.name: Masquerain

attacks.name: Struggle Bug
attacks.text: Move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

sm1.flavorText: Its wings and antennae don't cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.

sm1.name: Rowlet
sm1.flavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

sm1.name: Dartrix

attacks.name: Sharp Blade Quill
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

sm1.flavorText: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

attacks.name: Splashing Dodge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

abilities.name: Compound Eyes
abilities.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon do 50 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon that has an Ability (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shocking Web
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Lightning Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

attacks.name: Add On
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: United Wings
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

attacks.name: Stock Up on Feathers
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Power Shot
attacks.text: Discard a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand. If you can't, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Wood Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Snarl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 100 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Suction
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Anachronism Repulsor
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Ancient Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

xy7.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

xy7.flavorText: Its scientific name is "Oddium Wanderus." At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

xy7.name: Gloom
xy7.flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

xy7.name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Irritating Pollen
abilities.text: Each player can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.

xy7.flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

xy7.name: Bellossom

attacks.name: Windmill
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flower Tornado
attacks.text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

xy7.flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

xy7.name: Spinarak

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy7.flavorText: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

xy7.name: Ariados

abilities.name: Poisonous Nest
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. Both Active Pokémon (except for Grass Pokémon) are now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

xy7.flavorText: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

xy7.name: Sceptile-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Unseen Claw
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

xy7.name: M Sceptile-EX
rules: Mega Evolution rule: When 1 of your Pokémon becomes a Mega Evolution Pokémon, your turn ends.
Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ancientTrait.name: θ Stop
ancientTrait.text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokémon's Abilities done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Jagged Saber
attacks.text: You may attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, heal all damage from that Pokémon.

xy7.name: Combee
xy7.flavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

xy7.name: Vespiquen

attacks.name: Intelligence Gathering
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Bee Revenge
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.

xy7.flavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

xy10.name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Hide a Berry
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards. Then, put a card from your hand on the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy10.flavorText: It stores Berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

xy10.name: Burmy
xy10.flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

xy10.name: Wormadam

attacks.name: Solar Ray
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Leaf Cutter
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

xy10.flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

xy10.name: Mothim

abilities.name: Wormadam First
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Wormadam to another of your Pokémon.

xy10.flavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

xy10.name: Snivy

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

xy10.flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

xy10.name: Servine

abilities.name: Serpentine Strangle
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

xy10.flavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

xy10.name: Serperior

attacks.name: Coil
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's attacks do 60 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

xy10.flavorText: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

xy10.name: Deerling

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

xy10.flavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

xy10.name: Moltres

attacks.name: Flying Flare
attacks.text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

xy10.flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

xy10.name: Fennekin

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

xy10.flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

bw3.name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Leaf Boomerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

bw3.flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

bw3.name: Swadloon

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

bw3.flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

bw3.name: Leavanny

abilities.name: Leaf Tailor
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it has no Weakness.

attacks.name: Cutting Arm
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

bw3.flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

bw3.name: Petilil

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

bw3.flavorText: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

bw3.name: Lilligant

attacks.name: Aromax
attacks.text: Heal all damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Windmill
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

bw3.flavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.

bw3.name: Dwebble

attacks.name: Withdraw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

bw3.flavorText: The Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

bw3.name: Crustle

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

bw3.flavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

bw3.name: Karrablast

attacks.name: Mysterious Evolution
attacks.text: If Shelmet is in play, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

bw3.flavorText: When they feel threatened, they spit acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

bw3.name: Foongus
bw3.flavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

bw3.name: Amoonguss

attacks.name: Toxic
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

bw3.flavorText: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

abilities.name: Terraforming
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 5 cards from your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order. This power can't be used if Aggron is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Mix-Up
attacks.text: Your opponent discards the top card of his or her deck.

abilities.name: Synergy Effect
abilities.text: If Drake's Stadium is in play, remove 1 damage counter from Altaria between turns.

attacks.name: Surprise
attacks.text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at the card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Rock Blast
attacks.text: Discard up to 5 Fighting Energy cards attached to Armaldo. For each Energy card you discarded, choose an opponent's Pokémon in play and this attack does 20 damage to those Pokémon. (You may choose the same Pokémon more than once.) This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

attacks.name: Mach Claw
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Grudge
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

attacks.name: Bench Manipulation
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a number of coins equal to the number of his or her Benched Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage times the number of tails. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

abilities.name: Firestarter
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Blaziken is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Fire Stream
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Blaziken. This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Bursting Inferno
attacks.text: Each Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

abilities.name: Evolutionary Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Cradily from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for up to 3 in any combination of Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards. Show them to your opponent and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Poison Ring
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Energy Draw
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard 1 Energy card from your hand. Then draw up to 3 cards from your deck. This power can't be used if Delcatty is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Max Energy Source
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your Active Pokémon.
