abilities.name: Psy Shadow
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Burst
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the total amount of Energy attached to Gardevoir and the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Primal Stare
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards from his or her hand to evolve his or her Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Luring Antenna
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to the new Defending Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.

attacks.name: Retaliate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Aggron.

attacks.name: Double Lariat
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Withering Dust
abilities.text: As long as Beautifly is in play, do not apply Resistance for all Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Parallel Gain
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon, including Beautifly.

abilities.name: Firestarter
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Blaziken is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Fire Stream
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Blaziken. If you do, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Lava Burn
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 basic Energy cards attached to Camerupt or this attack does nothing.

abilities.name: Energy Draw
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard 1 Energy card from your hand. Then draw up to 3 cards from your deck. This power can't be used if Delcatty is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Max Energy Source
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your Active Pokémon.

abilities.name: Protective Dust
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, except damage, done to Dustox by the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Toxic
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on the Defending Pokémon between turns.

abilities.name: Psy Shadow
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Burst
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the total amount of Energy attached to Gardevoir and the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Super Slap Push
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mega Throw
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon-ex, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Attract Current
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Manectric does 10 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Intimidating Fang
abilities.text: As long as Mightyena is your Active Pokémon, any damage done to your Pokémon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shakedown
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

pop7.name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Jamming
abilities.text: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Cluster Bolt
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop7.flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

pop7.name: Gallade

attacks.name: Sonic Blade
attacks.text: Put damage counters on the Defending Pokémon until it is 50 HP away from being Knocked Out. If you do, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic Cut
attacks.text: You may choose as many of your face-down Prize cards as you like and put them face up. If you do, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Prize card you chose. (These cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

pop7.flavorText: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on it elbows.

pop7.name: Latias

attacks.name: Miraculous Light
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters and all Special Conditions from Latias.

attacks.name: Mist Ball
attacks.text: Discard a Fire and a Water Energy attached to Latias.

pop7.flavorText: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

pop7.name: Latios

attacks.name: Energy Draw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to Latios. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Luster Purge
attacks.text: Discard 3 Energy attached to Latios.

pop7.flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

pop7.name: Mothim

attacks.name: Silver Wind
attacks.text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Raging Scales
attacks.text: If Mothim has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 damage plus 40 more damage.

pop7.flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

pop7.name: Delibird

attacks.name: Present
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

pop7.flavorText: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

pop7.name: Flaaffy

attacks.name: Attract Current
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Electromagnetic Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Flaaffy does 10 damage to itself.

pop7.flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fire hair that zaps on impact.

pop7.name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Psychic Research
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack. (The Supporter card remains in your discard pile.)

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

pop7.flavorText: It is highly perceptive of its Trainer's feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.

pop7.name: Stantler

attacks.name: Lead
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Frighten Horn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon isn't an Evolved Pokémon, that Pokémon is now Confused.

pop7.flavorText: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

pop7.name: Wormadam Sandy Cloak

abilities.name: Sandy Cloak
abilities.text: Prevent all effects, excluding damage, done to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

attacks.name: Push Over
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Fighting Energy attached to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

pop7.flavorText: When BURMY evolved, it cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

base6.name: Alakazam

abilities.name: Damage Swap
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to another as long as you don't Knock Out that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

base6.flavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5000.

base6.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Freeze Dry
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base6.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

base6.name: Charizard

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard or this attack does nothing.

base6.flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

base6.name: Dark Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydrocannon
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Rocket Tackle
attacks.text: Dark Blastoise does 10 damage to itself. Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Dark Blastoise during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

base6.flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.

base6.name: Dark Dragonite

abilities.name: Summon Minions
abilities.text: When you play Dark Dragonite from your hand, search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Giant Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

base6.flavorText: Sometimes called "The God of Destruction." Its wings are able to support it in spite of its massive weight.

base6.name: Dark Persian

attacks.name: Fascinate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Poison Claws
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

base6.flavorText: Popular with women because of its beautiful fur. The leader of the Rockets keeps one as a pet.

base6.name: Dark Raichu

attacks.name: Surprise Thunder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, flip another coin. If the second coins is heads, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If the second coin is tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

base6.flavorText: Stores up electricity in its body, then suddenly releases it to surprise and shock everyone.

base6.name: Dark Slowbro

abilities.name: Reel In
abilities.text: When you play Dark Slowbro from your hand, choose up to 3 Basic Pokémon and/or Evolution cards from your discard pile and put them into your hand.

attacks.name: Fickle Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

base6.flavorText: It loves nothing better than to be left alone, and so sometimes ends up being manipulated by unscrupulous people.

base6.name: Dark Vaporeon

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Energy cards attached to it, choose 1 of them and discard it.

base6.flavorText: A Pokémon capable of controlling water, so it is capable of creating giant whirlpools.

base6.name: Flareon

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Flareon or this attack does nothing.

base6.flavorText: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

abilities.name: Energy Jump
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move an Energy card from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Energy Recharge
abilities.text: When you play Arcanine from your hand to evolve your Active Pokémon, you may flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose a basic Energy card from your discard pile and attach it to Arcanine.

attacks.name: Shake
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon, if any.

attacks.name: White Flames
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy cards attached to Arcanine.

abilities.name: Water Immunity
abilities.text: You can't attach Water Energy cards from your hand to Articuno.

attacks.name: Freeze Solid
attacks.text: If there are any Water Energy cards in your discard pile, flip a coin. If heads, attach 1 of them to Articuno.

attacks.name: Ice Cyclone
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Pokémon in play. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Venom Spray
abilities.text: When you play Beedrill from your hand to evolve your Active Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Needle Rush
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. If you get 1 heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If you get 2 heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage. If you get 3 heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 50 more damage. If you get 4 heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 90 more damage.

abilities.name: Carry Off
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent's hand. If your opponent has any Baby Pokémon, Basic Pokémon, or Evolution cards there, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck. This power can't be used if Crobat is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Double Cross
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. If both of them are tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Freeze Lock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't attach Energy cards from his or her hand to his or her Active Pokémon during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Crushing Ice
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Colorless Energy in the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost. Damage is calculated using the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost after applying effects to the Retreat Cost.

abilities.name: Self-healing
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to Flareon, remove all Special Conditions affecting Flareon.

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Burn Booster
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to Flareon in order to use this attack. If the discarded card is a Fire Energy card, this attack does 40 damage plus 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Spinning Blow
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. If both coins are heads, switch Forretress with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Scatterbomb
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, do 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. For each tails, do 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Manipulate
abilities.text: When you play Gengar from your hand to evolve your Active Pokémon, you may put a Basic Pokémon (excluding Baby Pokémon) from your discard pile onto your Bench. Then, flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose a basic Energy card from your discard pile and attach it to that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hydrokinesis
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

abilities.name: Flame Vapor
abilities.text: When you play Gyarados from your hand to evolve your Active Pokémon, you may flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragon's Vengeance
attacks.text: If Gyarados has 7 or more damage counters on it, this attack's base damage is 100.

swsh5.name: Bellsprout

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

swsh5.flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

swsh5.name: Weepinbell

abilities.name: Dangerous Mucus
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Burned and Poisoned.

swsh5.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

swsh5.name: Victreebel

attacks.name: Panic Vine
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

swsh5.flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

swsh5.name: Cacnea
swsh5.flavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

swsh5.name: Cacturne

attacks.name: Pull
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spiny Punch
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

swsh5.flavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

swsh5.name: Kricketune V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Exciting Stage
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand. If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand instead. You can't use more than 1 Exciting Stage Ability each turn.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

swsh5.name: Cherubi
swsh5.flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

swsh5.name: Cherrim

abilities.name: Spring Bloom
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't have a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).

swsh5.flavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

swsh5.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Big Bite
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Triple Whip
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

swsh5.flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

swsh5.name: Durant

attacks.name: Devour
attacks.text: For each of your Durant in play, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

swsh5.flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

col1.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Fairy Power
attacks.text: Return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it in your hand.

col1.flavorText: With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

col1.name: Deoxys

attacks.name: Cell Storm
attacks.text: Discard 2 Psychic Energy attached to Deoxys and remove 6 damage counters from Deoxys.

col1.flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

col1.name: Dialga

attacks.name: Time Rewind
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck.

col1.flavorText: This Pokémon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.

col1.name: Espeon

attacks.name: Solar Suggestion
attacks.text: Move up to 4 damage counters from any of your Pokémon to any of your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

col1.flavorText: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy's actions.

col1.name: Forretress

attacks.name: Mirror Shot
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Everyone Explode Now
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of Pineco and Forretress you have in play. This attack does 30 damage to each of your Pineco and Forretress in play.

col1.flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

col1.name: Groudon

attacks.name: Volcano Stomp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 4 cards of your opponent's deck. If tails, discard the top 4 cards of your deck.

col1.flavorText: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

col1.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

col1.flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

col1.name: Hitmontop

attacks.name: Triple Kick
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Hitmontop by attacks is increased by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

col1.flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

col1.name: Ho-Oh

attacks.name: Scorching Wing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Fire Energy attached to Ho-Oh.

col1.flavorText: Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world's skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.

col1.name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Fire Counterattack
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Fighting Pokémon in play, this attack does 20 damage plus 60 more damage.

attacks.name: Dark Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent discards a card from his or her hand.

col1.flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.text: Blaine's Arcanine does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Firestorm
attacks.text: Discard 3 Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Arcanine in order to use this attack.

attacks.name: Roaring Flames
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard. If all Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard provide 2 Fire Energy, discard all of them. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Flame Jet
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

abilities.name: Shapeshift
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach an Evolution card from your hand to Brock's Ninetales. (This doesn't count as evolving Brock's Ninetales.) Treat Brock's Ninetales as if it were that Pokémon instead. It can't evolve, devolve, or use the Pokémon Power of that Pokémon. During your turn, you may discard the Evolution card attached to Brock's Ninetales. This power can't be used if Brock's Ninetales is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Brock's Ninetales becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed, discard all Evolution cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, you may attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to Erika's Venusaur.

attacks.name: Wide Solarbeam
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 2 of them (or 1 if he or she only has 1). This attack does 20 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Summon Storm
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 20 damage to each other Pokémon (even your own). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack.

attacks.name: Dragon Tornado
attacks.text: Unless this attack Knocks Out the Defending Pokémon, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Fortitude
abilities.text: If Giovanni's Machamp would be Knocked Out by an opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, Giovanni's Machamp is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead. This power can't be used if Giovanni's Machamp is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hurricane Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Intimidate
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon's maximum HP is 50 or less, it can't attack Giovanni's Nidoking during your opponent's next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Tumbling Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage; if tails, this attack does 40 damage.

abilities.name: Call the Boss
abilities.text: When you play Giovanni's Persian from your hand, you may search your deck for the Trainer card named Giovanni, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Nerve Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Hyper Needle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. Either way, you can't use this attack again as long as Koga's Beedrill stays in play (even putting Koga's Beedrill on the Bench won't let you use it again).

attacks.name: Giant Growth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, Koga's Ditto's maximum HP is now 80 and Koga's Ditto's Pound attack's base damage is 30 instead of 10. (Benching Koga's Ditto ends this effect.)

sv6.name: Tangela
sv6.flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

sv6.name: Tangrowth

abilities.name: Thicket Body
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Loom Over
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

sv6.flavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

sv6.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Slow Crunch
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon will be Knocked Out.

sv6.flavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

sv6.name: Spinarak
sv6.flavorText: Some fishers weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

sv6.name: Sunflora

attacks.name: Redirected Sunlight
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage for each Fire Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

sv6.flavorText: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

sv6.name: Sunkern

attacks.name: Bullet Seed
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

sv6.flavorText: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

sv6.name: Ariados

abilities.name: Big Net
abilities.text: Your opponent's Active Evolution Pokémon's Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

attacks.name: String Bind
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

sv6.flavorText: It wanders in search of food after darkness falls, never nesting in a specific place.

sv6.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

sv6.flavorText: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

sv6.name: Volbeat

attacks.name: Quick Sign
attacks.text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Coordinated Strike
attacks.text: If Illumise is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage.

sv6.flavorText: It flashes the light on its rear to communicate with other Volbeat. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

sv6.name: Illumise

attacks.name: Slowing Perfume
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Shuffle 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

sv6.flavorText: It guides Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. There are scholars who research the meaning of these signs.

bw11.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Flog
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

bw11.flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

bw11.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Flog
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

bw11.flavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.

bw11.name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Share
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

bw11.flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

bw11.name: Cherubi

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

bw11.flavorText: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.

bw11.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Ambush Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

bw11.flavorText: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.

bw11.name: Snivy

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

bw11.flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

bw11.name: Servine

attacks.name: Wring Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

bw11.flavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

bw11.name: Serperior

abilities.name: Royal Heal
abilities.text: At any time between turns, heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Leaf Tornado
attacks.text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

bw11.flavorText: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

bw11.name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Leaf Boomerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

bw11.flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

bw11.name: Sewaddle
bw11.flavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

swsh4.name: Weedle

attacks.name: Bug Hunch
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh4.flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

swsh4.name: Kakuna

attacks.name: Shed Skin
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh4.flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

swsh4.name: Beedrill

abilities.name: Elusive Master
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is the last card in your hand, you may play it onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.

swsh4.flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

swsh4.name: Exeggcute
swsh4.flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

swsh4.name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Head Crack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

swsh4.flavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

swsh4.name: Yanma

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

swsh4.flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

swsh4.name: Yanmega

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

swsh4.flavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

swsh4.name: Pineco

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

swsh4.flavorText: It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.

swsh4.name: Celebi

attacks.name: Energy Press
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Amazing Bloom
attacks.text: For each of your Benched Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh4.flavorText: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.

swsh4.name: Seedot
swsh4.flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

bw7.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

bw7.flavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

bw7.name: Gloom

attacks.name: Foul Odor
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Confused.

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

bw7.flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

bw7.name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Allergy Panic
abilities.text: Apply Weakness for each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) as ×4 instead.

attacks.name: Pollen Spray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

bw7.flavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

bw7.name: Bellossom

bw7.flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

bw7.name: Tangela

attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

bw7.flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

bw7.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Hundred Furious Lashes
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the amount of Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon. This Pokémon can't use Hundred Furious Lashes during your next turn.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

bw7.flavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.

bw7.name: Scyther
bw7.flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

bw7.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Giga Horn
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

bw7.flavorText: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.

attacks.name: Wind Whisk
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

bw7.name: Shaymin

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

bw7.flavorText: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.

sv1.name: Scatterbug

abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

sv1.flavorText: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.

sv1.name: Pineco

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv1.flavorText: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

sv1.name: Cacturne

abilities.name: Counterattack Quills
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

sv1.flavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

sv1.name: Gogoat

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

sv1.flavorText: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.

sv1.name: Sprigatito
sv1.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

sv1.name: Meowscarada

attacks.name: Trick Cape
attacks.text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

sv1.flavorText: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

sv1.name: Tarountula

attacks.name: String Haul
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

sv1.flavorText: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon's natural enemy.

sv1.name: Tarountula

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

sv1.flavorText: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread's strength is the topic of ongoing research.

sv1.name: Smoliv
sv1.flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

sv1.name: Smoliv

attacks.name: Nutrients
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

sv1.flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

svp.name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Mini Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

svp.flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

svp.name: Fuecoco

attacks.name: Super Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

svp.flavorText: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

svp.name: Pawmot

abilities.name: Electrogenesis
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Electro Paws
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

svp.flavorText: Pawmot's fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.

svp.name: Espathra

attacks.name: Aurora Gain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

svp.flavorText: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.

svp.name: Hawlucha

abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and put 1 damage counter on each of them.

svp.flavorText: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.

svp.name: Miraidon

attacks.name: Lightning Laser
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

svp.flavorText: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

svp.name: Revavroom

abilities.name: Rumbling Engine
abilities.text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage.

svp.flavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.

svp.name: Spidops

attacks.name: String Truss
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

svp.flavorText: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

svp.name: Arcanine

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

svp.flavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

svp.name: Quaxly

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

svp.flavorText: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

sm11.name: Rowlet & Alolan Exeggutor-GX
rules: TAG TEAM rule: When your TAG TEAM is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Grass Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. If that Pokémon is now a Stage 1 Pokémon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokémon that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Calming Hurricane
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tropical Hour-GX
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), your opponent shuffles all Energy from all of their Pokémon into their deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

sm11.name: Yanma
sm11.flavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won't miss prey—even those behind it.

sm11.name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Air Slash
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

sm11.flavorText: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

sm11.name: Celebi

attacks.name: Time Spiral

sm11.name: Shroomish

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

sm11.flavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

sm11.name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Multiply
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Sewaddle and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm11.flavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

sm11.name: Sewaddle

abilities.name: Swaddling Leaves
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

sm11.flavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

sm11.name: Swadloon

abilities.name: Swaddling Leaves
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sm11.flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

sm11.name: Leavanny

abilities.name: Blanket Weaver
abilities.text: Your Grass Pokémon take 40 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Blanket Weaver Ability at a time.

sm11.flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

sm11.name: Dwebble
sm11.flavorText: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

sv4.name: Surskit

attacks.name: Triple Spin
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

sv4.flavorText: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

sv4.name: Masquerain

attacks.name: Daunting Eyes
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, shuffle an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their deck.

sv4.flavorText: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.

sv4.name: Froslass ex
rules: Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Frost Bullet

attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

sv4.name: Simisage

attacks.name: Arm Thrust Needle
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Pokémon that have an Ability, except any Simisage.

sv4.flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

sv4.name: Dwebble
sv4.flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

sv4.name: Crustle

attacks.name: Crag Bash
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 100 less damage from attacks from Evolution Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv4.flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.

sv4.name: Bounsweet

attacks.name: Quick Blow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

sv4.flavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled- down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

sv4.name: Steenee

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

sv4.flavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

sv4.name: Blipbug

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

sv4.flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

bw5.name: Bulbasaur
bw5.flavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

bw5.name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Poison Powder

bw5.name: Venusaur

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

bw5.flavorText: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

bw5.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Air Slash

bw5.flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

attacks.text: Your opponent puts the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her hand.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

bw5.flavorText: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.

bw5.name: Dwebble
bw5.flavorText: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

bw5.name: Crustle

attacks.name: Heavy Bullet
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

bw5.flavorText: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

bw5.name: Karrablast

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

bw5.flavorText: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

bw5.name: Shelmet

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

pop6.name: Bastiodon

abilities.name: Protective Wall
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by your opponent's attacks.

attacks.name: Anger Revenge
attacks.text: If Bastiodon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop6.flavorText: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

pop6.name: Lucario

attacks.name: Feint
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop6.flavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

pop6.name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Aqua Ring
attacks.text: Switch Manaphy with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

pop6.flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

pop6.name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Pachirisu does 10 damage to itself.

pop6.flavorText: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

pop6.name: Rampardos

attacks.name: Assurance
attacks.text: As long as the Defending Pokémon's remaining HP is 60 or less, this attack's base damage is 60 instead of 30.

attacks.name: Hasty Headbutt
attacks.text: Rampardos does 20 damage to itself. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

pop6.flavorText: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

pop6.name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Blowing Wind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Ominous Wind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused and can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

pop6.flavorText: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

pop6.name: Gible

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

pop6.name: Riolu

attacks.name: Wild Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

pop6.flavorText: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

pop6.name: Pikachu
rules: Oran Berry: Remove 1 damage counter from Pikachu at the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

pop6.name: Staravia

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

pop6.flavorText: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

swsh12.name: Venonat
swsh12.flavorText: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

swsh12.name: Venomoth

attacks.name: Miracle Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Condition. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition.

swsh12.flavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

swsh12.name: Spinarak
swsh12.flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

swsh12.name: Ariados

abilities.name: Hidden Threads
abilities.text: Your opponent's Pokémon VSTAR's attacks cost Colorless more. You can't apply more than 1 Hidden Threads Ability at a time.

swsh12.flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

swsh12.name: Sunkern
swsh12.flavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

swsh12.name: Sunflora

attacks.name: Bright Beam
attacks.text: You may discard up to 3 Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 70 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

swsh12.flavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

swsh12.name: Serperior V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Noble Light
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

swsh12.name: Serperior VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Regal Blender
attacks.text: You may move any amount of Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Star Winder
