swsh12.name: Petilil
swsh12.flavorText: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.

swsh12.name: Hisuian Lilligant

attacks.name: Swelling Scent
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh12.flavorText: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.

neo2.name: Espeon

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

neo2.flavorText: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy's actions.

neo2.name: Forretress

abilities.name: Spikes
abilities.text: During your opponent's turn, whenever 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon becomes his or her Active Pokémon, Forretress does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if Forretress is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Rapid Spin
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with his or her Active Pokémon, then, if you have any Benched Pokémon, you switch 1 of them with your Active Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

neo2.flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

neo2.name: Hitmontop

attacks.name: Detect
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Hitmontop.

attacks.name: Triple Kick
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

neo2.flavorText: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dancelike kicks, you may get drilled hard.

neo2.name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Houndoom or this attack does nothing.

neo2.flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

neo2.name: Houndour

attacks.name: Smog
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Collect Fire
attacks.text: If there are any Fire Energy cards in your discard pile, choose 1 of them and attach it to Houndour.

neo2.flavorText: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

neo2.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Hydrocutter
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards attached to Kabutops. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. You can't flip more than 3 coins in this way.

neo2.flavorText: In the water, it tucks its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

neo2.name: Magnemite

attacks.name: Lock-on
attacks.text: During your next turn, treat any tails flipped when using Magnemite's Electric Bolt attack as if they were heads. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Electric Bolt
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

neo2.flavorText: These Pokémon are attracted to electrical emissions and will often follow people using PokéGear.

neo2.name: Politoed

abilities.name: Frog Song
abilities.text: Whenever Politoed's attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), if there are more than 3 Poliwags, Poliwhirls, Poliwraths, and/or Politoeds in play (including your opponent's), that attack does 40 more damage (no matter how many heads you get). This power stops working while Politoed is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Doubleslap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

neo2.flavorText: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

neo2.name: Poliwrath

attacks.name: Submission
attacks.text: Poliwrath does 20 damage to itself.

neo2.flavorText: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.

neo2.name: Scizor

attacks.name: False Swipe
attacks.text: Does damage equal to half the Defending Pokémon's remaining HP (rounded down to the nearest 10).

attacks.name: Double Claw
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

neo2.flavorText: It swings its eye patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

mcd19.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

mcd19.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

mcd19.name: Alolan Exeggutor

attacks.name: Tropical Shake
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

mcd19.flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

mcd19.name: Magmar

attacks.name: Controlled Burn
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

mcd19.flavorText: When angered, it spouts brilliant fire from all over its body. It doesn't calm down until its opponent has burned to ash.

mcd19.name: Alolan Sandshrew

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

mcd19.flavorText: An ancient tradition of Alolan festivals, still carried on to this day, is a competition to slide Sandshrew across ice as far as one can.

mcd19.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Aqua Bullet
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

mcd19.flavorText: These Pokémon were once near extinction due to poaching. Following protective regulations, there is now an overabundance of them.

mcd19.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Iron Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

mcd19.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

mcd19.name: Gastly

attacks.name: Ominous Eyes
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

mcd19.flavorText: Should a strange light be seen flickering in an abandoned building, Gastly is lurking there.

mcd19.name: Mankey

attacks.name: Three-Step Strike
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

mcd19.flavorText: It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages, and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.

mcd19.name: Onix

attacks.name: Screech
attacks.text: During your next turn, the Defending Pokémon takes 20 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

mcd19.flavorText: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

mcd19.name: Alolan Meowth

attacks.name: Spoil the Fun
attacks.text: If you go second, this attack does 60 more damage during your first turn.

mcd19.flavorText: When its delicate pride is wounded, or when the gold coin on its forehead is dirtied, it flies into a hysterical rage.

swsh9tg.name: Flareon

abilities.name: Incandescent Awakening
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Grass Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

swsh9tg.flavorText: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

swsh9tg.name: Vaporeon

abilities.name: Torrential Awakening
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Fire Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

swsh9tg.flavorText: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

swsh9tg.name: Octillery

abilities.name: Rapid Strike Search
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Rapid Strike card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can't use more than 1 Rapid Strike Search Ability each turn.

swsh9tg.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

swsh9tg.name: Jolteon

abilities.name: Thunderous Awakening
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Water Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

swsh9tg.flavorText: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

swsh9tg.name: Zekrom

attacks.name: Wild Shock
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

swsh9tg.flavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.

swsh9tg.name: Dusknoir

abilities.name: Spectral Breach
abilities.text: All Special Energy attached to Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) provide Colorless Energy and have no other effect.

swsh9tg.flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

swsh9tg.name: Dedenne

attacks.name: Dede-Flash
attacks.text: If your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 60 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

swsh9tg.flavorText: Since Dedenne can't generate as much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.

swsh9tg.name: Alcremie

abilities.name: Additional Order
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your turn does not end when you use Café Master.

attacks.name: Rainbow Flavor
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each type of basic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

swsh9tg.flavorText: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

swsh9tg.name: Ariados

abilities.name: Spider Net
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Evolution Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

swsh9tg.flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

swsh9tg.name: Houndoom

abilities.name: Single Strike Roar
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Single Strike Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Single Strike Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

swsh9tg.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

sm8.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

sm8.flavorText: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

sm8.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Hefty Whip
attacks.text: If this Pokémon was healed during this turn, this attack does 130 more damage.

sm8.flavorText: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

sm8.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Fury Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 50 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 70 more damage.

sm8.flavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

sm8.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Grip and Squeeze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

sm8.flavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

sm8.name: Chikorita

attacks.name: Synthesis
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm8.flavorText: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

sm8.name: Chikorita

attacks.name: Mini Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

sm8.flavorText: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

sm8.name: Bayleef

attacks.name: Soothing Scent
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

sm8.flavorText: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

sm8.name: Meganium

abilities.name: Quick-Ripening Herb
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card onto the Basic Pokémon to evolve it. You can use this Ability during your first turn or on a Pokémon that was put into play this turn.

sm8.flavorText: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

sm8.name: Spinarak

attacks.name: Spider Scram
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned. Put this Pokémon and all cards attached to it in the Lost Zone.

sm8.flavorText: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

sm8.name: Ariados

attacks.name: Trapping Thread
attacks.text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand during their next turn, prevent all effects of that card done to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

sm8.flavorText: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

abilities.name: Flare Condition
abilities.text: As long as Arcanine has any Fire Energy attached to it, Arcanine has no Weakness.

attacks.name: Burn Out
attacks.text: You may do 30 damage plus 30 more damage. If you do, Arcanine is now Burned.

attacks.name: Flames of Rage
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Arcanine. This attack does 60 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Arcanine.

attacks.name: Bounce Back
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Smack Attack
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Bastiodon GL.

abilities.name: Eerie Aura
abilities.text: Put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon that remains Asleep between turns.

attacks.name: Darkness Sleep
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, that Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Incite
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 Supporter cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand.

attacks.name: Giant Wave
attacks.text: Floatzel GL can't use Giant Wave during your next turn.

abilities.name: Rainbow Float
abilities.text: If any basic Energy card attached to Flygon is the same type as any of your Pokémon, the Retreat Cost for those Pokémon is 0.

attacks.name: Sand Wall
attacks.text: Discard a Stadium card your opponent has in play. If you do, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Flygon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Power Swing
attacks.text: Does 60 damage plus 10 more damage for each Evolved Pokémon on your Bench.

attacks.name: Sleep Inducer
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. The new Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Wake-Up Slap
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is affected by any Special Conditions, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage. Then, remove all Special Conditions from the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Final Wish
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Jirachi would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Detour
attacks.text: If you have a Supporter card in play, use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Boundary Aura
abilities.text: Apply Weakness for each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) as ×2 instead.

attacks.name: Combo Throw
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Trash Bolt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card from your hand. (If you can't discard a card from your hand, this attack does nothing.)

attacks.name: Psychic Removal
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, discard all Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Grudge
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

cel25.name: Ho-Oh

attacks.name: Sacred Fire
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

cel25.flavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.

cel25.name: Palkia

abilities.name: Absolute Space
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Stadium cards from their hand.

attacks.name: Overdrive Smash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overdrive Smash attack does 80 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

cel25.flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

cel25.name: Reshiram

attacks.name: Scorching Wind
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Black Flame
attacks.text: If Zekrom is on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

cel25.flavorText: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

cel25.name: Flying Pikachu VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Max Balloon
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.

cel25.name: Kyogre

attacks.name: Aqua Storm
attacks.text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck, and then choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way to each of those Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cel25.flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

cel25.name: Xerneas

attacks.name: Breath of Life
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards of different types and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

cel25.flavorText: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

cel25.name: Surfing Pikachu V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

cel25.name: Cosmoem

attacks.name: Star Protection
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

cel25.flavorText: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

cel25.name: Surfing Pikachu VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Max Surfer
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cel25.name: Lunala

attacks.name: Lunar Pain
attacks.text: Double the number of damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic Shot
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cel25.flavorText: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

dc1.name: Team Magma's Numel

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

dc1.flavorText: No matter how heavy the cargo, we can transport it to our destination with ease, thanks to Numel.

dc1.name: Team Magma's Camerupt

abilities.name: Burning Draft
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fighting or Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flame Ball
attacks.text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

dc1.flavorText: Camerupt, with its strength against fire, played a big role in rescuing team members.

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Spheal
dc1.flavorText: Spheal's Water Gun can put out any fire. Flames used by opponents have no effect!

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Sealeo

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Hail Storm
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Team Magma Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.

dc1.flavorText: It provides support by making paths of ice. It can win any battle as long as it's on ice.

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Walrein

attacks.name: Power Blow
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dual Blizzard
attacks.text: Discard 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dc1.flavorText: It's good at attacks that freeze opponents with a powerful cold snap. Then, it pulverizes a frozen foe with its sharp tusks!

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Kyogre-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Power Saver
abilities.text: If there are 4 or fewer Team Aqua Pokémon in play, this Pokémon can't attack.

attacks.name: Aqua Impact
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Grimer
dc1.flavorText: Its flexible body, which allows it to squeeze into any cracks, comes in handy when invading enemy hideouts.

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Muk

abilities.name: Sludge Festival
abilities.text: The Retreat Cost of each Pokémon in play (except for Team Aqua Pokémon) is Colorless more.

attacks.name: Pester
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 60 more damage.

dc1.flavorText: It immobilizes its opponents by wrapping them in its huge, poisonous body. It'll smoosh you, too!

dc1.name: Team Aqua's Seviper

attacks.name: Venomous Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Venom Tail
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, discard an Energy attached to that Pokémon.

dc1.flavorText: Seviper's tail is a sharp blade. It can even poison you!

dc1.name: Team Magma's Baltoy

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

dc1.flavorText: They all cry out at once to let us know when they spot an enemy. It really helps out!

dv1.name: Dratini

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

dv1.flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

dv1.name: Dratini

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

dv1.flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

dv1.name: Dragonair

attacks.name: Dragon Pulse
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your deck.

dv1.flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

dv1.name: Dragonair

attacks.name: Healing Melody
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

dv1.flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

dv1.name: Dragonite

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hurricane Tail
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

dv1.flavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

dv1.name: Bagon
dv1.flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

dv1.name: Shelgon

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

dv1.flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

dv1.name: Salamence

abilities.name: Scornful Storm
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent discard cards from his or her hand until he or she has 4 cards left in his or her hand.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

dv1.flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

dv1.name: Latias

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sky Heal
attacks.text: If Latios is on your Bench, heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

dv1.flavorText: Its body is covered in a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

dv1.name: Latios

attacks.name: Sky Blade
attacks.text: If Latias is on your Bench, this attack does 20 more damage.

dv1.flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

cel25c.name: Charizard

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard in order to use this attack.

cel25c.flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

cel25c.name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokémon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Extra Water Energy after the 2nd doesn't count.

cel25c.flavorText: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

cel25c.name: Venusaur

abilities.name: Energy Trans
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Grass Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon and attach it to a different one. This power can't be used if Venusaur is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

cel25c.flavorText: This plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

cel25c.name: Here Comes Team Rocket!
rules: Each player plays with his or her Prize cards face up for the rest of the game.

abilities.name: Cosmic Power
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose up to 2 cards from your hand and put them on the bottom of your deck in any order. If you do, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Claydol is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.text: If there are any Lightning Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Rocket's Zapdos.

attacks.name: Electroburn

sm115.name: Butterfree
sm115.flavorText: Its wings are covered in toxic scales. If it finds bird Pokémon going after Caterpie, Butterfree sprinkles its scales on them to drive them off.

sm115.name: Paras
sm115.flavorText: Whether it's due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don't grow up quite right.

sm115.name: Scyther
sm115.flavorText: Its two sharp scythes are more than just weapons. It uses them with dexterity to dress its prey before eating.

sm115.name: Pinsir-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Guillotine-GX
attacks.text: (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

sm115.name: Charmander
sm115.flavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

sm115.name: Charmeleon
sm115.flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

sm115.name: Charizard-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Flare Blitz-GX
attacks.text: (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

sm115.name: Magmar
sm115.flavorText: Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!

abilities.name: Shadow Command
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may draw 2 cards. If you have 7 or more cards in your hand, discard a number of cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. Then, put 2 damage counters on Dusknoir. This power can't be used if Dusknoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Damage Even
attacks.text: Count the number of damage counters on Dusknoir. Put that many damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Night Spin
attacks.text: Prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Dusknoir by your opponent's Pokémon that has 2 or less Energy attached to it during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Emperor Aura
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you play Empoleon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Active Pokémon, you may use this power. Your opponent can't attach any Energy cards from his or her hand to his or her Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Steel Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Empoleon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Blaze Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you play Infernape from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 4 Fire Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Infernape by attacks is increased by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Spreading Fire
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Infernape and this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Fin Luster
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Lumineon is your Active Pokémon, you may look at your opponent's hand. If your opponent's Bench isn't full, choose 1 Basic Pokémon from your opponent's hand, and put it onto his or her Bench. Then, switch it with the Defending Pokémon. This power can't be used if Lumineon is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Quick Swim
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

attacks.name: Elegant Swim
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Lumineon during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Magnetic Search
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Lightning or Metal Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Magnezone is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Speed Shot
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crush Volt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to Magnezone.

dp7.name: Magnezone

abilities.name: Super Connectivity
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your discard pile for a Lightning or Metal Energy card and attach it to your Active Pokémon. Then, put 1 damage counter on that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Magnezone is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Gyro Ball
attacks.text: You may switch Magnezone with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

dp7.flavorText: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

attacks.name: Crash Chant
attacks.text: Choose up to 4 in any combination of Pokémon Tool cards and Technical Machine cards in play (both yours and your opponent's) and discard them. This attack does 20 damage times the number of cards discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Horror Chant
attacks.text: If your opponent has 4 or more Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and return that Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Slice
attacks.text: Raichu can't use Slice during your next turn.

attacks.name: Split Ball
attacks.text: Move an Energy card attached to Raichu to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Burst Ball
attacks.text: Discard 3 Energy attached to any of your Pokémon in any way you like.

abilities.name: Regi Form
abilities.text: If you have Regirock, Regice, and Registeel in play, the attack cost of Regigigas's attacks is Colorless less.

attacks.name: Giga Power
attacks.text: You may do 60 damage plus 40 more damage. If you do, Regigigas does 40 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Energy Trans
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), move a Grass Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Sceptile is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Poison Leaf
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Slice Drain
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Sceptile.

bw4.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Power Pinch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Grip and Squeeze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

bw4.flavorText: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.

bw4.name: Seedot

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

bw4.flavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

bw4.name: Kricketot

attacks.name: Double Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 more damage for each heads.

bw4.flavorText: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

bw4.name: Kricketune

attacks.name: White Noise
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Draining Cut
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

bw4.flavorText: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.

bw4.name: Shaymin-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Synthesis
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Revenge Blast
attacks.text: Does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

bw4.name: Pansage
bw4.flavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

bw4.name: Simisage

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Stadium Drain
attacks.text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 30 more damage and heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

bw4.flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

bw4.name: Foongus

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

bw4.flavorText: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

bw4.name: Amoonguss

abilities.name: Sporprise
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may use this Ability. If you do, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

bw4.flavorText: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

bw4.name: Growlithe

attacks.name: Stoke
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Firebreathing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

bw4.flavorText: A Pokémon with a loyal nature, it will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

hsp.name: Ho-Oh

attacks.name: Sacred Fire
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

hsp.flavorText: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind when it flies.

hsp.name: Lugia

attacks.name: Aeroblast
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

hsp.flavorText: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

hsp.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Recharge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Pikachu. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy attached to Pikachu.

hsp.flavorText: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

hsp.name: Wobbuffet

abilities.name: Tenacious Bind
abilities.text: As long as Wobbuffet is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost is ColorlessColorless more.

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 30 more damage.

hsp.flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

hsp.name: Hoothoot

abilities.name: Insomnia
abilities.text: Hoothoot can't be Asleep.

hsp.flavorText: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.

hsp.name: Noctowl

abilities.name: Night Scope
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at your opponent's hand. This power can't be used if Noctowl is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

hsp.flavorText: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Water Energy from your hand to 1 of your Water Pokémon. This power can't be used if Feraligatr is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Crunch
attacks.text: Does 60 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on the Defending Pokémon.

abilities.name: Leaf Trans
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Grass Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Meganium is affected by a Special Condition.

abilities.name: Afterburner
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your discard pile for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. If you do, put 1 damage counter on that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Typhlosion is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Flare Destroy
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to Typhlosion and discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

hsp.name: Latias

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Infinite Wind
attacks.text: If Latios is on your Bench, remove 2 damage counters from each of your Benched Pokémon.

hsp.flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

swsh11.name: Oddish
swsh11.flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

swsh11.name: Gloom

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh11.flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

swsh11.name: Vileplume

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Allergy Storm
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Supporter cards from their hand. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

swsh11.flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

swsh11.name: Paras

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh11.flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

swsh11.name: Parasect

abilities.name: Lethargy Spores
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may make both Active Pokémon Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

swsh11.flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

swsh11.name: Wurmple

attacks.name: Creepy-Crawly Congregation
attacks.text: Search your deck for any number of Wurmple, Silcoon, Beautifly, Cascoon, and Dustox, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh11.flavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

swsh11.name: Silcoon

attacks.name: Entangling String
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

swsh11.flavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

swsh11.name: Beautifly

abilities.name: Stoked Straw
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh11.flavorText: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

swsh11.name: Cascoon

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks if that damage is 60 or less.

swsh11.flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

swsh11.name: Dustox

attacks.name: Nadir Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 8 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

swsh11.flavorText: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.

abilities.name: Blaze
abilities.text: As long as Blaziken's remaining HP is 40 or less, Blaziken does 40 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Damage Burn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for another Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys. (Any cards attached to Deoxys, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Power, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Throw
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 60 damage plus 40 more damage.

abilities.name: Heal Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Heal Dance Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

attacks.name: Rock Tumble
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Aqua Sonic
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tail Shock
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Super Hypno Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Dragon Dance
attacks.text: During your next turn, if any of your current Active Pokémon does damage to any Defending Pokémon, the attack does 30 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

abilities.name: Green Essence
abilities.text: As long as Sceptile is in play, each of your Active Pokémon that has Grass Energy attached to it can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

mcd16.name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

mcd16.flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

mcd16.name: Torchic

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

mcd16.flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

mcd16.name: Fennekin
mcd16.flavorText: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

mcd16.name: Magikarp

attacks.name: Epic Splash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

mcd16.flavorText: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

mcd16.name: Totodile

attacks.name: Fury Strikes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

mcd16.flavorText: It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

mcd16.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

mcd16.flavorText: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

mcd16.name: Scraggy
mcd16.flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling it skin up to its neck.

mcd16.name: Jigglypuff

attacks.name: Heartfelt Song
attacks.text: Discard a Darkness Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

mcd16.flavorText: It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.

mcd16.name: Togepi

attacks.name: Sweet Kiss
attacks.text: Your opponent draws a card.

mcd16.flavorText: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.

mcd16.name: Dedenne

attacks.name: Nuzzle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

mcd16.flavorText: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

sm5.name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Continuous Eggsplosion
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

sm5.flavorText: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.

sm5.name: Yanma

attacks.name: Super Speed
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

sm5.flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

sm5.name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

sm5.flavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

sm5.name: Roselia

attacks.name: Petal Dance
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads. This Pokémon is now Confused.

sm5.flavorText: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

sm5.name: Roserade

attacks.name: Inviting Poison
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Flower Tornado
attacks.text: Move any number of Grass Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

sm5.flavorText: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

sm5.name: Turtwig

attacks.name: Synthesis
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm5.flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

sm5.name: Turtwig
sm5.flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

sm5.name: Grotle

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

sm5.flavorText: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

sm5.name: Torterra

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

sm5.flavorText: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

sm5.name: Cherubi

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

sm5.flavorText: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

np.name: Kyogre ex
rules: When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Major Flood
attacks.text: Discard a Water Energy card attached to Kyogre ex. Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

np.name: Groudon ex
rules: When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Major Earthquake
attacks.text: Discard a Fighting Energy card attached to Groudon ex. Does 10 damage to your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Poison Breath
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
