attacks.name: Fireworks
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Torchic.

attacks.name: Fireworks
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Torchic.

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

dp5.name: Articuno

abilities.name: Freezing Screech
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Articuno from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dp5.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

dp5.name: Cresselia

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

attacks.name: Healing Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon.

dp5.flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

dp5.name: Darkrai

abilities.name: Darkness Shade
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Darkrai from your hand onto your Bench, you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Dark Slumber
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Dark Resolve
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, remove 4 damage counters from Darkrai.

dp5.flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

dp5.name: Dialga
rules: Adamant Orb: If an Active Pokémon has Weakness to Metal type, Dialga's attacks do 20 more damage to that Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Time Shift
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Diamond Blast
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

dp5.name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Snow Cloak
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Glaceon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Speed Slide
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

dp5.flavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

dp5.name: Kabutops

abilities.name: Primal Shell
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Chop Up
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

dp5.flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

dp5.name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Leaf Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Leafeon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

dp5.flavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

dp5.name: Manaphy

abilities.name: Aqua Skin
abilities.text: When you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Manaphy, remove 2 damage counters from Manaphy.

attacks.name: Chase Up
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Fountain
attacks.text: You may attach up to 2 basic Water Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

dp5.flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

dp5.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Energy Absorption
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 Energy cards and attach them to Mewtwo.

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard a Psychic Energy attached to Mewtwo and remove 6 damage counters from Mewtwo.

dp5.flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

dp5.name: Moltres

abilities.name: Flame Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Moltres from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for up to 3 Fire Energy cards and attach them to Moltres.

attacks.name: Scorching Wing
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Moltres.

dp5.flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

bw6.name: Hoppip

attacks.name: Flail Around
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

bw6.flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

bw6.name: Skiploom

attacks.name: Bullet Seed
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

bw6.flavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

bw6.name: Jumpluff

abilities.name: Leave It to the Wind
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may return this Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

bw6.flavorText: Blown by the seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

bw6.name: Yanma

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

bw6.flavorText: It can hover in one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.

bw6.name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

bw6.flavorText: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

bw6.name: Wurmple

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

bw6.flavorText: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

bw6.name: Silcoon

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 60 or less.

bw6.flavorText: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

bw6.name: Beautifly

attacks.name: Triple Energy
attacks.text: Search your deck for 3 different types of basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Drainpour
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

bw6.flavorText: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

bw6.name: Cascoon

attacks.name: Tangle Drag
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

bw6.flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

bw6.name: Nincada

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

bw6.flavorText: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

mcd18.name: Horsea

attacks.name: Water Arrow
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

mcd18.flavorText: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

mcd18.name: Psyduck

attacks.name: Confusion Wave
attacks.text: Both Active Pokémon are now Confused.

mcd18.flavorText: As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.

mcd18.name: Growlithe

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

mcd18.flavorText: It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.

mcd18.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Pika Draw
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

mcd18.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

mcd18.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Whimsy Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

mcd18.flavorText: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn't really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn't particularly bothered.

mcd18.name: Machop
mcd18.flavorText: It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.

mcd18.name: Cubone

attacks.name: Leer
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

mcd18.flavorText: When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.

mcd18.name: Chansey

attacks.name: Bind Wound
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

mcd18.flavorText: The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.

mcd18.name: Magnemite

attacks.name: Searching Magnet
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Metal Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

mcd18.flavorText: It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it's eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.

mcd18.name: Dratini

attacks.name: Signs of Evolution
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Dratini, a Dragonair, and a Dragonite, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

mcd18.flavorText: After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.

sm3.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

sm3.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

sm3.name: Metapod

attacks.name: Shed Skin
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

sm3.flavorText: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.

sm3.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Bye-Bye Heal
attacks.text: Heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. Shuffle this Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your deck.

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

sm3.flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.

sm3.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

sm3.flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

sm3.name: Gloom

attacks.name: Stinky Scent
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

sm3.flavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

sm3.name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Disgusting Pollen
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Basic Pokémon can't attack.

attacks.name: Downer Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

sm3.flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

sm3.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

sm3.flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

sm3.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crosswise Whip
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

sm3.flavorText: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

sm3.name: Ledyba

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

sm3.flavorText: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.

sm3.name: Ledian

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

sm3.flavorText: While it's believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.

sm6.name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Multiply
attacks.text: Search your deck for Exeggcute and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm6.flavorText: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokémon. It's often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.

sm6.name: Alolan Exeggutor

attacks.name: Tropical Shake
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

sm6.flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

sm6.name: Alolan Exeggutor

attacks.name: Tropical Shake
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

sm6.flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

sm6.name: Snover

attacks.name: Ice Shard
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Fighting Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

sm6.flavorText: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

sm6.name: Abomasnow

abilities.name: Blessings of the Frost
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may attach a Grass Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hypno Hammer
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

sm6.flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

sm6.name: Scatterbug

abilities.name: Abnormal Outbreak
abilities.text: You can use this Ability only if you go second. Once during your first turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Spewpa and a Vivillon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm6.flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

sm6.name: Scatterbug

attacks.name: Ultra Evolution
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for Vivillon and put it onto this Scatterbug to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

sm6.flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

sm6.name: Spewpa

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

sm6.flavorText: The beaks of birds can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

sm6.name: Vivillon

attacks.name: Vivid Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

sm6.flavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

sm6.name: Skiddo

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.text: Attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.

sm6.flavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

xy2.name: Caterpie

abilities.name: Adaptive Evolution
abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

xy2.flavorText: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.

xy2.name: Metapod

abilities.name: Adaptive Evolution
abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 60 or less.

xy2.flavorText: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

xy2.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Quiver Dance
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward. If you attached Energy in this way, heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

xy2.flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

xy2.name: Pineco
xy2.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

xy2.name: Seedot

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

xy2.flavorText: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

xy2.name: Nuzleaf
xy2.flavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

xy2.name: Shiftry

abilities.name: Leaf Draw
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Grass Energy card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Deranged Dance
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

xy2.flavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

xy2.name: Roselia

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

xy2.flavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

xy2.name: Roserade

attacks.name: Whiplash
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

xy2.flavorText: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.

xy2.name: Maractus

attacks.name: Exciting Shake
attacks.text: During your next turn, flip 6 coins instead of 2 for this Pokémon's Prickly Needles attack.

attacks.name: Prickly Needles
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

xy2.flavorText: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.text: Arcanine does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Damage Burn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Drawup Power
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Front Spark
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Firebreathing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage.

tk2b.name: Celio's Network
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card (excluding Pokémon-ex), show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

tk2b.name: Energy Search
rules: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward

tk2b.name: Potion
rules: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon (remove 1 damage counter if that Pokémon has only 1).

mcd12.name: Servine

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

mcd12.flavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

mcd12.name: Pansage

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

mcd12.flavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

mcd12.name: Dwebble

attacks.name: Withdraw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

mcd12.flavorText: The Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

mcd12.name: Pignite

attacks.name: Flame Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

mcd12.flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

mcd12.name: Dewott

attacks.name: Razor Shell
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

mcd12.flavorText: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

mcd12.name: Emolga

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

mcd12.flavorText: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membranes and released while it is gliding.

mcd12.name: Woobat

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

mcd12.flavorText: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

mcd12.name: Drilbur

attacks.name: Hone ClawsScratch
attacks.text: During your next turn, each of this Pokémon's attacks does 30 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

mcd12.flavorText: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

mcd12.name: Purrloin

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

mcd12.flavorText: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

mcd12.name: Scraggy
mcd12.flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

swsh3.name: Butterfree V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dizzying Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

swsh3.name: Butterfree VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: G-Max Toxbreeze
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

swsh3.name: Paras
swsh3.flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

swsh3.name: Parasect

attacks.name: Mushroom Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

swsh3.flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

swsh3.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Return
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

swsh3.flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

swsh3.name: Pansage
swsh3.flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

swsh3.name: Simisage

attacks.name: Giga Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

swsh3.flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

swsh3.name: Karrablast

attacks.name: Continuous Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

swsh3.flavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

swsh3.name: Shelmet
swsh3.flavorText: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

swsh3.name: Accelgor
swsh3.flavorText: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

mcd14.name: Chespin
mcd14.flavorText: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

mcd14.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Nuzzle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

mcd14.flavorText: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

mcd14.name: Inkay
mcd14.flavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

mcd14.name: Furfrou

attacks.name: Tight Jaw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

mcd14.flavorText: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

mcd14.name: Weedle

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

mcd14.flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

mcd14.name: Froakie
mcd14.flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

mcd14.name: Honedge

attacks.name: Continuous Slash
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

mcd14.flavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

mcd14.name: Snubbull
mcd14.flavorText: It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.

mcd14.name: Bunnelby
mcd14.flavorText: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

mcd14.name: Fletchling

attacks.name: Razor Wind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

mcd14.flavorText: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

mcd15.name: Treecko

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

mcd15.flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

mcd15.name: Lotad
mcd15.flavorText: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

mcd15.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

mcd15.flavorText: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

mcd15.name: Zigzagoon

attacks.name: Sand Attack
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

mcd15.flavorText: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.

mcd15.name: Torchic

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

mcd15.flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

mcd15.name: Meditite
mcd15.flavorText: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

mcd15.name: Marill
mcd15.flavorText: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

mcd15.name: Mudkip
mcd15.flavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

mcd15.name: Rhyhorn

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

mcd15.flavorText: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.

mcd15.name: Staryu

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

mcd15.flavorText: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

attacks.name: Reactive Poison
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 30 more damage for each Special Condition affecting the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spider Trap
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned. Before applying this effect, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. If you do, the new Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.

abilities.name: Energy Connect
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon. This power can't be used if Ampharos is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Miraculous Thunder
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

attacks.name: Green Dance
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Pokémon, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If you put any Grass Pokémon into your hand, you may switch Bellossom with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Full Bloom
attacks.text: If you have at least 3 Bellossom in play, this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.

abilities.name: Intimidating Fang
abilities.text: As long as Feraligatr is your Active Pokémon, any damage done by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Pull Away
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 of more cards in his or her hand, your opponent discards a number of cards until your opponent has 4 cards left in his or her hand.

attacks.name: Tonnage
attacks.text: You may do 50 damage plus 30 more damage. If you do, Feraligatr does 30 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Fire Dance
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Multi Burn
attacks.text: If Flareon has 3 or more different types of basic Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Attract Current
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Multi Pulse
attacks.text: If Jolteon has 3 of more different types of basic Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Spiky Shell
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon at the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Pop
attacks.text: Put 7 damage counters on Forretress. Move all Energy cards attached to Forretress to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. (Ignore this effect if you don't have any Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Lonesome
abilities.text: As long as you have less Pokémon in play than your opponent, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards (except for Supporter cards) from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Tight Jaw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Houndoom.

abilities.name: Super Suction Cups
abilities.text: As long as Octillery is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Standing By
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to Octillery. During your next turn, Octillery's Pulse Blast attack's base damage is 120.

abilities.name: Spiral Swirl
abilities.text: If Poliwrath is your Active Pokémon and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, the Attacking Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Beatdown
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Darkness Pokémon or has Dark in its name, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Hyper Splash
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Stage 2 Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 60 damage plus 30 more damage.

neo1.name: Ampharos

attacks.name: Gigaspark
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

neo1.flavorText: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

neo1.name: Feraligatr

abilities.name: Berserk
abilities.text: When you play Feraligatr from your hand, flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 5 cards from your opponent's deck. If tails, discard the top 5 cards from your deck.

attacks.name: Chomp
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of damage counters on Feraligatr. This attack does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

neo1.flavorText: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

neo1.name: Azumarill

attacks.name: Bubble Shower
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

neo1.flavorText: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.

neo1.name: Bellossom

attacks.name: Sweet Nectar
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flower Dance
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of cards with Bellossom in their names that you have in play (including this one).

neo1.flavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

neo1.name: Feraligatr

abilities.name: Downpour
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Water Energy card from your hand. This power can't be used if Feraligatr is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Riptide
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 damage times the number of Water Energy cards in your discard pile. Then, shuffle all Water Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

neo1.flavorText: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

neo1.name: Heracross

abilities.name: Final Blow
abilities.text: If Heracross's remaining HP are 20 or less, you may make its Megahorn attack's base damage 120 instead of 60. This power can't be used if Heracross is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Megahorn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

neo1.flavorText: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies, then lifts and throws them.

neo1.name: Jumpluff

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: If this attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), remove 1 damage counter from Jumpluff, if it has any.

neo1.flavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.

neo1.name: Lugia

attacks.name: Elemental Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card, a Water Energy card, and a Lightning Energy card attached to Lugia in order to use this attack.

neo1.flavorText: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea, because its powers are too strong.

neo1.name: Kingdra

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Kingdra.

attacks.name: Dragon Tornado
attacks.text: If this attack doesn't Knock Out the Defending Pokémon, and if there are any Pokémon on your opponent's Bench, choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokémon.

neo1.flavorText: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

neo1.name: Meganium

abilities.name: Herbal Scent
abilities.text: When you play Meganium from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from all Grass Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

neo1.flavorText: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

swsh45sv.name: Rowlet

abilities.name: Sky Circus
abilities.text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.

attacks.name: Wind Shard
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

swsh45sv.flavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.

swsh45sv.name: Dartrix
swsh45sv.flavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

swsh45sv.name: Blipbug
swsh45sv.flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

swsh45sv.name: Applin

attacks.name: Withdraw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

swsh45sv.flavorText: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.

swsh45sv.name: Centiskorch

attacks.name: Hundred Foot Flames
attacks.text: For each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

swsh45sv.flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

swsh45sv.name: Suicune

attacks.name: Aurora Loop
attacks.text: Put 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

swsh45sv.flavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

swsh45sv.name: Sobble
swsh45sv.flavorText: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

swsh45sv.name: Drizzile

abilities.name: Shady Dealings
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh45sv.flavorText: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

swsh45sv.name: Inteleon

abilities.name: Shady Dealings
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Aqua Bullet
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

swsh45sv.flavorText: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

swsh45sv.name: Rillaboom

abilities.name: Voltage Beat
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

swsh45sv.flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

hgss1.name: Arcanine
hgss1.flavorText: This legendary Chinese Pokémon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

hgss1.name: Azumarill

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

hgss1.flavorText: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

hgss1.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Fairy Power
attacks.text: Return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

hgss1.flavorText: With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

hgss1.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

hgss1.flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

hgss1.name: Hitmontop

attacks.name: Triple Kick
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Hitmontop by attacks is increased by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

hgss1.flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

hgss1.name: Jumpluff

attacks.name: Mass Attack
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Leaf Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Jumpluff by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

hgss1.flavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores—it can even float around the world.

hgss1.name: Ninetales

abilities.name: Roast Reveal
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Fire Energy card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards. This power can't be used if Ninetales is affected by a Special Condition.

hgss1.flavorText: Its nine beautiful tails are filled with a wondrous energy that could keep it alive for 1,000 years.

hgss1.name: Noctowl

abilities.name: Night Sight
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may draw a card. This power can't be used if Noctowl is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Extrasensory
attacks.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

hgss1.flavorText: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

hgss1.name: Quagsire

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

hgss1.flavorText: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

hgss1.name: Shuckle

abilities.name: Shell Barricade
abilities.text: As long as Shuckle is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to Shuckle by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

hgss1.flavorText: The berries it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

abilities.name: Reactive Protection
abilities.text: Any damage done to Aerodactyl by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon is reduced by 10 for each React Energy card attached to Aerodactyl (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Power Blow
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Aerodactyl.

attacks.name: Speed Stroke
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects, including damage, done to Aerodactyl by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon-ex.

attacks.name: Devolution Wave
attacks.text: Count the number of React Energy cards attached to Cradily and choose up to that number of your opponent's Evolved Pokémon. Remove the highest Stage Evolution card from each of those Pokémon, then have your opponent shuffle those cards into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Linear Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Heavy Blow
attacks.text: Does 70 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Aggron. If Aggron has any React Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 70 damage instead.

attacks.name: Bound Crush
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) During your next turn, Aggron can't use Bound Crush.

abilities.name: Reactive Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move a React Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Delcatty is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Link
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for an Energy card and attach it to Delcatty.

abilities.name: Shadow Curse
abilities.text: If Gengar would be Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Cursed Reaction
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like. If Gengar has any React Energy cards attached to it, put 4 damage counters instead.

abilities.name: Support Navigation
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Lapras onto your Bench from your hand, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

abilities.name: Ancient Shell
abilities.text: As long as you have Omanyte or Omastar in play, damage done to Kabutops by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Energy Stream
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to Kabutops.

attacks.name: Extra Claws
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Mend
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Fighting Energy card and attach it to Golem. If you do, remove 2 damage counters from Golem.

attacks.name: Enraged Linear Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on Golem to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Rock Tumble
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Derail
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy card, if any, attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Swift Blow
attacks.text: Does 60 damage plus 20 damage for each React Energy card attached to Machamp.

abilities.name: Stench
abilities.text: As long as Muk is your Active Pokémon, each player's Pokémon can't use any Poké-Powers.

attacks.name: Poison Ring
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

pgo.name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Summoning Aroma
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

pgo.flavorText: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

pgo.name: Radiant Venusaur
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

abilities.name: Sunny Bloom
abilities.text: Once at the end of your turn (after your attack), you may use this Ability. Draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Pollen Hazard
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

pgo.flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

pgo.name: Ariados

attacks.name: Poison String-Up
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokémon.

pgo.flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

pgo.name: Charmander

attacks.name: Tail on Fire
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

pgo.flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

pgo.name: Charmeleon

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

pgo.flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

pgo.name: Radiant Charizard
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

abilities.name: Excited Heart
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

attacks.name: Combustion Blast
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Combustion Blast.

pgo.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

pgo.name: Golisopod

attacks.name: First Impression
attacks.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

pgo.flavorText: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

pgo.name: Lunatone

attacks.name: Cycle Draw
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Moon Kinesis
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

pgo.flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.

pgo.name: Sylveon

attacks.name: Souvenir
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Wonder Flash
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Dragon Pokémon, this attack does 90 more damage.

pgo.flavorText: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.

pgo.name: Alolan Raticate

attacks.name: Chase Up
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Super Fang
attacks.text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

pgo.flavorText: It commands a nest of Rattata. Different nests don't get along, whipping up severe fights over feeding grounds.

abilities.name: Primal Veil
abilities.text: As long as Armaldo is your Active Pokémon, each player can't play any Supporter Cards.

abilities.name: Super Suction Cups
abilities.text: As long as Cradily is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Lure Poison
attacks.text: Before using this effect, you may switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon, if any. The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Cradily (remove 1 if there is only 1).

abilities.name: Poison Payback
abilities.text: If Cacturne is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Cacturne is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Judgement
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Random Curse
attacks.text: Put a total of 5 damage counters on all Defending Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Super Singe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Flareon.

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Lightning Strike
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Jolteon. If you do, this attack's base damage is 70 instead of 40.

abilities.name: Rain Dish
abilities.text: At any time between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Ludicolo.

attacks.name: Hydro Punch
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Ludicolo but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

abilities.name: Lunar Eclipse
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Solrock is in play, you may use this power. Until the end of your turn, Lunatone's type is Darkness. This power can't be used if Lunatone is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Cosmic Draw
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Evolved Pokémon in play, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Scam
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. You may have your opponent shuffle a Supporter card you find there into his or her deck. If you do, your opponent draws a card.

attacks.name: Metal Hook
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to the new Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Supernatural
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. You may use the effect of a Supporter card you find there as the effect of this attack. (The Supporter card remains in your opponent's hand.)

attacks.name: Dark Bind
attacks.text: You may discard a Darkness Energy card attached to Sableye. If you do, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

swsh1.name: Celebi V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Line Force
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

swsh1.name: Roselia

attacks.name: Sweet Scent
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

swsh1.flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

swsh1.name: Roselia

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh1.flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

swsh1.name: Cottonee
swsh1.flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

swsh1.name: Roserade

attacks.name: Paralyze Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is also Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

swsh1.flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

swsh1.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Cotton Ride
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

swsh1.flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

swsh1.name: Durant

attacks.name: Bite Together
attacks.text: If Durant is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage.

swsh1.flavorText: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

swsh1.name: Maractus

attacks.name: Powerful Needles
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

swsh1.flavorText: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

swsh1.name: Grookey
swsh1.flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

swsh1.name: Dhelmise V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Anchor Anger
attacks.text: If any of your Grass Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

attacks.name: Giga Hammer
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Giga Hammer.

sm12.name: Venusaur & Snivy-GX
rules: TAG TEAM rule: When your TAG TEAM is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Shining Vine
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, when you attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to it, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Solar Plant-GX
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

sm12.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Sweet Scent
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

sm12.flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

sm12.name: Gloom

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

sm12.flavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

sm12.name: Vileplume-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Fragrant Flower Garden
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 30 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Massive Bloom
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Allergic Explosion-GX
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Paralyzed, and Poisoned. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

sm12.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Toxic
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

sm12.flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

sm12.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Grass Knot
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

sm12.flavorText: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

sm12.name: Sunflora

attacks.name: Solar Power
attacks.text: During your next turn, ignore all Energy in the attack costs of Grass Pokémon and Fire Pokémon. (This includes Pokémon that come into play on that turn.)

sm12.flavorText: As the hot season approaches, the petals on this Pokémon's face become more vivid and lively.

sm12.name: Sunkern

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

sm12.flavorText: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.

sm12.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Riled Horn
attacks.text: If your opponent has any TAG TEAM Pokémon in play, this attack does 70 more damage.

sm12.flavorText: It's proud of its thick horn. In Alola, its biggest rival is Vikavolt, which it's always fighting with.

sm12.name: Lileep

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

sm12.flavorText: In ancient times, it lived in warm seas. It disguised itself as seaweed to ambush its prey and devoured them whole when they got close.

sv5.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike.

sv5.flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

sv5.name: Pineco
sv5.flavorText: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

sv5.name: Seedot

attacks.name: Rigidify
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv5.flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

sv5.name: Nuzleaf

attacks.name: Comet Slap
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

sv5.flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

sv5.name: Shiftry

attacks.name: Expelling Tornado
attacks.text: Choose 3 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If you do, shuffle all of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that you didn't choose, and all cards attached to those Pokémon, into their deck.

attacks.name: Energy Loop
attacks.text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

sv5.flavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

sv5.name: Shroomish

attacks.name: Double Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

sv5.flavorText: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

sv5.name: Breloom

attacks.name: Knuckle Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

sv5.flavorText: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

sv5.name: Roselia

abilities.name: Poison Point
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

sv5.flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

sv5.name: Roserade

abilities.name: Poison Point
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

sv5.flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

sv5.name: Turtwig

abilities.name: Solid Shell
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

sv5.flavorText: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

abilities.name: Psymimic
abilities.text: Once during your turn, instead of Alakazam's normal attack, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks. Alakazam copies that attack including its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type that Pokémon is, Alakazam's type is still Psychic.) This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Syncroblast
attacks.text: If Alakazam and the Defending Pokémon don't have the same number of Energy cards attached to them, this attack's base damage is 20 instead of 80.

abilities.name: Energy Connect
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Benched Pokémon and attach it to your Active Pokémon. This power can't be used if Ampharos is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Lightning Strike
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack's base damage is 80 instead of 40.

abilities.name: Miraculous Powder
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove all Special Conditions from your Active Pokémon. This power can't be used if Butterfree is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from Butterfree.

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Poison Reaction
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

abilities.name: Jet Stream
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Blastoise is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to Blastoise, if any. Then, if there are any Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokémon, choose 1 of them and discard it. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Cannon
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy Cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

abilities.name: Moonlight
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put a card from your hand back on your deck. If you do, search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Clefable is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Doubleslap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Lick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Auto Fire
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Burning Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all basic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Scorching Whirlwind
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If 1 of them is tails, discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard. If both are tails, discard all Energy cards attached to Charizard.

attacks.name: Magnitude
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.
